ESPHome BLE Keyboard — send_string character test strings
==========================================================
Copy the test line for your active keyboard_layout and pass it to send_string.
Every character on the line is reachable by send_string without modifier toggling.

=== US Layout (95 chars) ===
 !"#$%&'()*+,-./0123456789:;<=>?@ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ[\]^_`abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz{|}~

=== UK Layout (98 chars) ===
 !"#$%&'()*+,-./0123456789:;<=>?@ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ[\]^_`abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz{|}~£¬€

=== DE Layout (117 chars) ===
 !"#$%&'()*+,-./0123456789:;<=>?@ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ[\]^_`abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz{|}~äöüÄÖÜß§°€µ²³´@[]{}\|~

Notes
-----
US  : full printable ASCII (0x20–0x7E).
UK  : US + £ (Shift+3)  ¬ (AltGr+`)  € (AltGr+4).
DE  : US + umlauts/special chars (äöüÄÖÜß§°€µ²³´) + AltGr symbols (@[]{}\\|~).
      send_string resolves all DE characters via UTF-8 lookup — the AltGr modifier
      is handled internally; no manual modifier toggle is needed.
